## Platform Operator Password Management

(For SupaBein operators — not end-users of apps built on SupaBein.)

```bash
# Change password while logged in
curl -s -X PATCH "$SUPABEIN_URL/api/v1/auth/password" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $SUPABEIN_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"current_password":"old","new_password":"new-password"}'

# Forgot password — generates a reset token
curl -s -X POST "$SUPABEIN_URL/api/v1/auth/forgot" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"you@example.com"}'
# returns { token: "abc123...", expires_in: 3600 }

# Reset with token
curl -s -X POST "$SUPABEIN_URL/api/v1/auth/reset" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"token":"abc123...","password":"new-password"}'
```

